	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree totally....work on all three skills simultaneously while you still melee a bit. Once you get to 20 or so, you'll find your armor class is so poor compared to other classes that you just wont want to wade in there anymore. At 31, the only time I swing a weapon is when the MoB is down to a sliver of health and I am exceedingly LOM.<br><br>If you are going to let any of them slide, I would go with 2hb, as you will want to get a ToV for your off-hand slot. I know there is a rarely-dropped mace in Kith Forest&nbsp;&nbsp;that is something like +8 WIS, so that is reason alone to get 2hb up there. Yes, there are a few 2hb weaps that add wis (Staff of Observers come to mind), but you'd be sacrificing the +10 from the ToV to get the +5 from the SoO, so you'd face a net loss of mana.<br><br>I personally still use a Combine Scimitar (lousy damage, but fast) in primary hand and a ToV in secondary. Yes, my max damage is only 13 points- and that very rarely- but my spells hit for 177 DD and a bit over 200 DoT, so it's obvious I'm no tank.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
