	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 15th 7:31 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been camping the bandits behind the bandit hill in West Karanas for a while now.<br><br>Primary benefits:<br><br>1) Bandit sashes.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a great quest for both exp and loot.  Turning them in to Chesguard at Qeynos pally guild will get you a bronze weap, gold, silver, and good exp.<br><br>2) Bronze weapons.  Quite often the bandits will have bronze spears, bronze main gauches, etc.<br><br>3) Coin.  I usually loot several gold off the bandits.<br><br>4) Exp.  These guys give excellent exp for this level range!<br><br>5) Not usually camped.<br><br>Strategy: <br><br>1) Wait until camp is fully popped and then harmonize.  Usually takes two or three casts.  I wait until the camp is fully popped so I don't get any nasty surprises after I snare a bandit.  <br><br>2) Pick a human bandit and snare it.  Human is important because the other races don't have the bandit sashes.<br><br>3) Run to the west and cast ignite until bandit dies or you run out of mana.  Melee if necessary.<br><br>If you happen to pull two bandits instead of just one with your snare, don't worry.  One is snared already.  Just run off a bit, snare the second one, and hightail it over to the Qhills zone.<br><br>Have fun!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
