	   <tr><td colspan=2>These are fine if you are a druid who likes to group .. personally I liked soloing aviaks durring this time. But I did get a tip from a fellow druid about these gnolls and was never able to try this because spires are camped most of the time.<br><br>At lvl 34 you get an area effect spell Lightening Strike, once you get this then head out and try and find an empty spire and you can solo 3 of these gnolls. First snare them all and start your kiting, instead of wasting mana on dots or direct damages use your new area effect spell on them which has a damage close to your direct damage but hits all the mobs you pull as long as they are close enough in proximity.<br><br>This is wonderful experience from what I've been told but it doesnt last real long since the gnolls will start to con green to you in about 2-3lvl(approx) after you get your lvl 34 spells. Also at lvl 34 you get another area effect spell, Earthquake, but im not sure how effective it will work in this process.<br><br>Safe journeys and good hunting!<br>&nbsp;<br>Sowin Masheen<br>60th Heirophant<br>Mithaniel Marr</td></tr>
