	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 2:09 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I had to choose my specialization, I though to myself, "What spell am I likely to cast in a pinch that will win or lose my/a groupmate's life?"<br><br>Let's cover the most poular:<br><br>Evocation - killing the mob before he kills you/your groupmate- undeniably needed sometimes.<br><br>Alteration - This one is most often referred to as healing- but let's not forget what else uses alteration, perhaps the most important job a druid has at high levels- EVAC.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is probably the spell that will save you and your group more than anything else.<br><br>Conjuration - doesn't really apply unless they you/your group is dying of hunger or thirst (woo!  Summon water!)<br><br><br>Thus (as you may have guessed) I chose alteration.  I prefer to get that last heal off when the cleric is oom or be able to evac when you're really low on mana.<br><br>Anyway, just my two cents.<br><br>Ervyn Peregrinus<br>40th Druid of Tunare<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Reality is for those who can't face Science Fiction</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
