<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9670668625414></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9670668625414><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9670668625414>RE: Choosing your specialization</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9670668625414#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=321><span id= >Quimby</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 23rd 5:41 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think many people forget what specialization does.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's a skill check inwhich a successful "roll" means the amount of mana used is less.  It doesn't reduce your casting cost, nor does it , for the most part, improve the way your spell works.  It can however help reduce fizzles for spells that require a high skill check.  But most of these are limited to VERY high level (50+ mostly) spells.  Spells like Evacs are not even in the spectrum as a need for specialization. As you still cannot cast the spell unless you have the proper mana, it's a lower level spell in which your skill check should be no problem, and the only bonus would be you may end up with some extra mana AFTER the evac.<br><br>Your specialization should be in a skill you use simply most often. Thus allowing you to ultimately save the most mana possible along the way. If you are a healer, then Alteration is the way to go.  If you are a nuker then Evocation is. Conjuration doesn't seem to be an issue to me as you aren't going to be chain casting any DoT unless using the root / DoT / med method of soloing.<br>&nbsp;<br>Quimby Thistlebritches<br>Druid of Karana<br><br>Sacred Order of Shadows</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

